Important Notice for FIGSiM developers and end-users:

i) If applicable, please cite our publications. Here is a starting point:
  + the reaction field/ellipsoid dielectric:
      Lewis E. Johnson, Robin Barnes, Thomas W. Draxler, Bruce E. Eichinger,
      and Bruce H. Robinson: "Dielectric Constants of Simple Liquids:
      Stockmayer and Ellipsoidal Fluids",
      J. Phys. Chem. B 114, 25, 8431-8440 (2010)
  + the Adiabatic Volume Adjustment (AVA) method:
      Andreas F. Tillack, Lewis E. Johnson, Meghana Rawal, Larry R. Dalton,
      and Bruce H. Robinson: "Modeling Chromophore Order: A Guide For
      Improving EO Performance", Symposium II/JJ/KK - Materials, Processe and
      Devices for Nanophotonics, Nonlinear Optics and Resonant Optics;
      MRS Online Proceedings Library, Vol. 1698, Cambridge University Press (2014)
  + the Ellipsoids/Level-of-Detail (LoD) method:
      Andreas F. Tillack, Lewis E. Johnson, Bruce E. Eichinger, and
      Bruce H. Robinson: "Systematic Generation of Anisotropic Coarse-Grained
      Lennard-Jones Potentials and Their Application to Ordered Soft Matter",
      J. Chem. Theory Comput. 12, 9, 4362-4374 (2016)
  + further relevant papers may include:
      R. D. Nielsen, H. L. Rommel, and B. H. Robinson: "Simulation of the
      Loading Parameter in Organic Nonlinear Optical Materials",
      J. Phys. Chem. B, 108, 25, 8659-8667 (2004)
      Harrison L. Rommel and Bruce H. Robinsonm: "Orientation of Electro-optic
      Chromophores under Poling Conditions: A Spheroidal Model",
      J. Phys. Chem. C, 111, 50, 18765-18777 (2007)
  + Dissertations of the developers listed below are publically available

ii) The original programs developed by Andreas F. Tillack, Lewis E. Johnson,
Bruce H. Robinson and their collaborators are distributed under
UIUC/NCSA Open Source License (below).

iii) Some packages/features included are under different open source license
and are marked appropriately in their code files.

